remediation:
It is recommended to create a StringBuilder (if JDK >= 1.5 and not in thread environment) or StringBuffer before entering the loop, and append to it within the loop, thus reducing the overhead.

The JVM is optimizing code such as 

System.out.println("x:"+x+" y:"+y);

by 

System.out.println((new StringBuilder()).append("x:").append(x).append(" y:").append(y).toString());

remediationSample:
Remediation for Sample#1

StringBuffer result = new StringBuffer("hello");
for (int i = 0; i < 1500; i++) {
   result.append("hello");  // FIXED
}

Remediation for Sample#2

StringBuffer sb = new StringBuffer("JDBC Connection parameters were : \n");
        for (String prop: props.stringPropertyNames())
        {
            if ("password".equalsIgnoreCase(prop) || "pwd".equalsIgnoreCase(prop))
                continue;

            sb.append("{").append(prop).append(" : ");  //Resolved
        }

